<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1207">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.116/170a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-28">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>The <hi rend="italic">North Carolina</hi> now at Falmouth has been
                            ordered to start to-morrow for Turkish waters with $150,000 gold relief
                                fund.<note n="1" xml:id="d1207fn1">The <hi rend="italic">Tennessee</hi> was sent later under similar orders.</note>
                            Department has notified Straus, Schiff, and other interested parties to
                            this effect who will probably send additional funds.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>